Citations
Date:  0/0/1980
Source:  Personal Kiwi-Yankee Dictionary, A
Author:  LELAND
Vol / Page:  18
Edition:
Quote:  <i>brown derby</i>: A CONE, usually OF plain (vanilla) ICE CREAM, with the ice cream part DIPPED IN hot CHOCOLATE which quickly hardens around it. Very tasty. This term is used only in the South Island. It is a chocolate dip in the North Island.
